Commentary: back of a length and outside off, Smith pushes at it with those hard hands, gets a thick edge down to the third man boundary
Commentary_short: Hastings to Smith, FOUR runs

Commentary: length, outside off, out comes the slog but Hastings gets away with it
Commentary_short: Hastings to Smith, no run

Commentary: shapes to sweep, but the ball not only beats Tamim but also the wicketkeeper as well. The quicker ball, meant to cramp the left-hander, goes awry
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Tamim Iqbal, 5 wides

Commentary: on the pads again as Tamim goes back to flick. Only connects with pad
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Tamim Iqbal, no run

Commentary: looks to scoop a length ball on leg stump, just gets enough bat for a single
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Tamim Iqbal, 1 run

Commentary: the arm ball, and it's through him! It's the slider, pitching on middle and hurtling through the gap between bat and pad. Smith is playing for spin. His bat might as well be in the adjacent pin code. Totally deceived
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Smith, OUT
Dismissal_text: DR Smith  b Mohammad Nawaz 23 (14b 4x4 1x6) SR: 164.28

Commentary: full on off stump, drives back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: nudges a full delivery through midwicket
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run

Commentary: massive appeal for lbw as Tamim goes for the sweep. The umpire shakes his head, possibly because it pitches outside leg. But Nawaz convinces his captain to go for a review. He is bowling over the wicket, and HawkEye confirms it doesn't pitch in line.
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Tamim Iqbal, no run

Commentary: flatter delivery outside off, punches it through cover
Commentary_short: Hassan Khan to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run

Commentary: strides down the pitch and mauls the length ball outside off over long-off. Doesn't get all of it, but these are short boundaries here
Commentary_short: Hassan Khan to Tamim Iqbal, SIX runs

Commentary: clips it off his toes through square leg
Commentary_short: Hassan Khan to Tamim Iqbal, 1 run

Commentary: gets down the pitch and taps the ball down to long-on
Commentary_short: Hassan Khan to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run

Commentary: whips a fullish delivery on leg stump through to deep square leg
Commentary_short: Hassan Khan to Tamim Iqbal, 1 run

Commentary: goes back and pushes the flatter delivery on off stump through to long-off
Commentary_short: Hassan Khan to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run

Commentary: drives the full delivery to long-off
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run

Commentary: flatter delivery on middle, works it to midwicket
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Tamim Iqbal, no run

Commentary: turns it deftly through square leg
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Tamim Iqbal, 1 run

Commentary: charges out of his crease and smashes a length ball down to long-off
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run

Commentary: dropped, but the deflection off the inside edge is so massive, and it's dying on Sarfraz as well. He actually does brilliantly to stay low enough to stop four runs. And with Tamim haring down the pitch, he also tries to stump him, but that doesn't pan out either
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Tamim Iqbal, no run

Commentary: backs away and punches it through extra cover
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Tamim Iqbal, 1 run

Commentary: lobs off the pad to midwicket. Maybe there is an inside edge there too
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Tamim Iqbal, 1 leg bye

Commentary: good length on off stump, blocks
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: full and on off stump, pushes it down the pitch
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: hoists it over extra cover, perfectly in the gap. A couple of steps down the pitch to hit through the line of the length ball
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Mohammad Hafeez, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length and outside off, chops it down by his feet.
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: goes for the bouncer, the batsman lets it go, and it climbs a little too high for the umpire's liking
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 wide

Commentary: full on off stump, turns it back down the pitch
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, tapped towards the leg side but can't take the run
Commentary_short: Hastings to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: back of a length but wide outside off, tries to carve this square off the back foot, but can't connect. Goes over the top of his blade to the keeper
Commentary_short: Hastings to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: good length outside off stump, just a bit of extra bounce this time, punched square past cover point to the man in the deep
Commentary_short: Hastings to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run

Commentary: full on leg stump, clipped comfortably off his pads to fine leg in the deep
Commentary_short: Hastings to Tamim Iqbal, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length wide outside off, but stays low! Tries to drag his pull towards the leg side but the ball zips under his bat. Goes to Sarfraz on the bounce
Commentary_short: Hastings to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: slower ball to end the over. Good length outside off and looops over Hafeez's head
Commentary_short: Hastings to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: back of a length on off stump, stands tall and taps it square to midwicket. They scamper across for the single
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Tamim Iqbal, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle and leg, slightly cramps Hafeez up. Worked off his pads to deep backward square. Played off the back foot
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run

Commentary: good length on off stump, easily whipped off his legs to midwicket. The man's there, but Tamim's swift enough to race across
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Tamim Iqbal, 1 run

Commentary: drifts slightly too much down the leg side, and it's been put away. Full outside leg, and tucked fine down the leg side. Runs it down past the keeper's left for a boundary
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Mohammad Hafeez, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on off stump and angling across the right hander, driven with soft hands to mid off for a quick run
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run

Commentary: goes short on off stump, but Tamim's up to the challenge! Emphatically pulled off the back foot in front of square. Deep backward square has no chance
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Tamim Iqbal, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length on middle and leg, slower ball to start the over. Hafeez is deceived by the lack of pace as he can't flick it towards the leg side. Hits his front leg, and they walk across for a leg bye
Commentary_short: Hastings to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 leg bye

Commentary: full on leg stump, bat-padded fine down the leg side to fine leg
Commentary_short: Hastings to Tamim Iqbal, 1 run

Commentary: good length outside off stump, angling into Hafeez. Stays on the back foot and taps it with the bat's open face to point
Commentary_short: Hastings to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, it's slightly too short this time. Hafeez tries to poke at it, but can't reach it. Almost a wide, to be honest
Commentary_short: Hastings to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: good length on middle and leg, cramps Hafeez with the batsman running down the wicket. Can only manage to nudge it towards the leg side. Smart bowling
Commentary_short: Hastings to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run

Commentary: full just outside leg stump, nudged with soft hands towards the gap on the leg side. Tamim will keep strike
Commentary_short: Hastings to Tamim Iqbal, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, angling across Tamim. Pushed off the back foot to cover point with ease
Commentary_short: Watson to Tamim Iqbal, 1 run

Commentary: tries to improvise, but can't get any reward. It's full outside off, but Hafeez tries to premeditate a ramp shot. Can only paddle to short fine leg
Commentary_short: Watson to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: slower ball, full on leg stump. Chipped over midwicket, but played softly enough so as to not carry to the man in the deep. Falls short of Asad
Commentary_short: Watson to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run

Commentary: almost chopped on! Full on off stump and Tamim tries to glance this fine. Bottom edges it as the ball bounces over the top of off stump. So close. The ball, in the first place, was too close to his body for that shot anyway
Commentary_short: Watson to Tamim Iqbal, no run

Commentary: full on middle and off, shuffles across to the off side and turns it towards midwicket
Commentary_short: Watson to Tamim Iqbal, 1 run

Commentary: full on middle stump, chips it over midwicket once again for a walking single. Hafeez will keep strike. These two making the chase look real simple here
Commentary_short: Watson to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run

Commentary: A monster, says the TV commentator, and I agree! Full and wide outside off, and it's been slogged over the bowler's head. Picked the cross-seam delivery early and it's been drilled into the stands beyond long-on. What's more, it's been taken by the fan in the crowd!
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Mohammad Hafeez, SIX runs

Commentary: good length outside off stump, opens the bat's face and runs it down to point
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: good length wide outside off, chopped down to third man in the deep
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, defended off the back foot past the non-striker. Played gently enough for them to scamper across for the single
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Tamim Iqbal, 1 run

Commentary: short outside off stump. Does well to deceive Hafeez with the extra pace. Tries to pull but was too late to get into that shot. One bouncer for the over
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: good length on off stump, shuffles across to the off side and turns it to square leg. Time for the strategic time out
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run

Commentary: good length wide outside off, Hafeez tries to tee off but can't connect. Goes just past his outside edge and through to Sarfraz. A dot to start the over
Commentary_short: Hastings to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: leading edge, and taken by Hasan! Full on off stump, and he tries to work it towards midwicket. The bat turns in his hand, and the edge is taken by point. Safe hands!
Commentary_short: Hastings to Mohammad Hafeez, OUT
Dismissal_text: Mohammad Hafeez c Hassan Khan b Hastings 29 (34b 2x4 1x6) SR: 85.29

Commentary: full on off stump, and that's been flicked excellently off the front foot. Runs it down to deep backward square, forcing the fielder in the deep to run across to his left
Commentary_short: Hastings to Sabbir Rahman, 2 runs

Commentary: back of a length on off stump, gets big on him. Tries to flick towards square leg, but can't connect. Hits his rib cage and falls near his toes
Commentary_short: Hastings to Sabbir Rahman, no run

Commentary: full on off stump, shaping into the batsman. Defended towards mid off
Commentary_short: Hastings to Sabbir Rahman, no run

Commentary: good length outside off, tapped off the front foot to cover. They can't take a single
Commentary_short: Hastings to Sabbir Rahman, no run

Commentary: full on off stump, angling across his body and driven on the up to long off. Played along the carpet
Commentary_short: Watson to Tamim Iqbal, 1 run

Commentary: full on off stump, swings into his body. Nudged off his pads towards deep backward square. Nice, late tail
Commentary_short: Watson to Sabbir Rahman, 1 run

Commentary: full on leg stump, tries to drive down the ball's line, and it has taken the outside edge. Tamim wants two, but third man - Anwar Ali - is quick to slide and throw the ball back. Tamim's struggling, and he's run out! Sarfraz is quick to take the bails off and the Aleem Dar doesn't even go up to the third umpire. Harakiri running, and this has, once again, brought some life back to this game!
Commentary_short: Watson to Tamim Iqbal, 1 run, OUT
Dismissal_text: Tamim Iqbal run out (Anwar Ali/†Sarfaraz Ahmed) 36 (38b 3x4 1x6) SR: 94.73

Commentary: good length outside off stump, tails into Usman. Defended back to Watto
Commentary_short: Watson to Khalid Usman, no run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, runs down the wicket trying to cut square, but he's in no position. Misses the shot completely. That's his 13th dot ball!
Commentary_short: Watson to Khalid Usman, no run

Commentary: misfield! Will earn them a run. Short outside off, and cut hard to third man. Wobbly effort from the man there
Commentary_short: Watson to Khalid Usman, 2 runs

Commentary: full on middle stump, walks down the wicket and turns it to deep midwicket. Played softly enough for them to comfortably take the second
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Sabbir Rahman, 2 runs

Commentary: full on middle and off, straightens slightly after pitching. Sabbir defends it back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Sabbir Rahman, no run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, sliding straight through. Sabbir rocks back and punches to long on
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Sabbir Rahman, 1 run

Commentary: good length wide outside off, plays late and cuts it to point. Slight misfield, allowing them to take a single
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Khalid Usman, 1 run

Commentary: tossed up on leg stump, comfortably flicked off his toes to deep backward square. Quetta won't mind these
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Sabbir Rahman, 1 run

Commentary: full outside off stump, comes down the wicket and slogs towards the leg side. Mistimed to cow corner
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Khalid Usman, 1 run

Commentary: yorker on off stump, can only manage to drill it to deep extra cover. Quetta won't mind this at all
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Khalid Usman, 1 run

Commentary: cheeky! Guides it fine down the leg side for a much-needed boundary. It's almost a yorker on middle stump, but the batsman opens his bat's face and paddles it fine. Excellent
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Sabbir Rahman, FOUR runs

Commentary: is it going for a six? Nope, holes out! Viv Richards is high-fiving everyone in the dug out. It was a log full toss on middle stump, and he slogs it towards the leg side. Hit well, but not well enough. Taken in the deep.
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Sabbir Rahman, OUT
Dismissal_text: Sabbir Rahman c Umar Amin b Rahat Ali 11 (11b 1x4 0x6) SR: 100.00

Commentary: back of a length on leg stump. Cramped for room, and he misses the pull shot. Through to the keeper in a flash
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Khalid Usman, no run

Commentary: full on middle stump, comes down the wicket and muscles it to mid on. Darren Sammy hops across to the other end. He's clearly struggling
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Khalid Usman, 1 run

Commentary: stand and deliver! So what if he can't run! Just stands on his spot and sends this full ball over the long-on boundary. Full enough for Sammy to get under this, and sends it into the stands! Ten needed off the final over
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Sammy, SIX runs

Commentary: low full toss outside off, mistimes his slog towards the leg side. Trickles down to cow corner, but it's only a single with the captain struggling
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Khalid Usman, 1 run

Commentary: Sammy, you beauty! This man is a phenom! Short on middle stump, and it's been pulled over deep backward square. Swivels and sends this over the ropes. The bowler misses the length, and Sammy punishes it. Viv Richards nods his head in disbelief
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Sammy, SIX runs

Commentary: excellent follow up ball, yorker on middle stump. Dug back to mid off but they can't take the single. Sammy says no for the run
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Sammy, no run

Commentary: Out come everybody to hug their captain! Courageous stuff from Darren Sammy. He's won them this game from nowhere. Full on off stump, and it's drilled down the ground. Mid off can't stop it and it's celebrations in the Peshawar camp. This is extraordinary. We don't know if we'll see Darren Sammy for the next game, but hats off to him for the resolve. Whoa. Peshawar Zalmi win by five wickets
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Sammy, FOUR runs
